{"id":286,"date":"2023-03-14T13:46:45","date_gmt":"2023-03-14T05:46:45","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost\/BSU-Open%20University\/?page_id=286"},"modified":"2023-06-23T08:26:46","modified_gmt":"2023-06-23T00:26:46","slug":"master-in-non-formal-education","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"http:\/\/localhost\/bsu-open%20university\/index.php\/programs-offered\/master-in-non-formal-education\/","title":{"rendered":"MASTER IN NON-FORMAL EDUCATION"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p class=\"has-text-align-left\">           Nonformal Education known as the Adult and Community Education (ACE) is an instrument of eradicating illiteracy. It becomes an agent of people\u2019s empowerment and transformation process geared towards poverty alleviation as well as improvement of the quality of life. The program intends to equip adult educators and related practitioners with necessary skills in the management and delivery of equal access to the basic educational services to the masses. Nonformal or Alternative Learning System (ALS) educators will be oriented with the alternative modes and andragogical strategies essential for adult and community education. Formal school teachers are likewise encouraged to commit themselves not only in the school but also in community extension services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-vivid-red-color has-text-color\"><b style=\"color:red\"><a href=\"http:\/\/localhost\/bsu-open%20university\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/MNFE-Brochure.pdf\" data-type=\"URL\" data-id=\"http:\/\/localhost\/bsu-open%20university\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/MNFE-Brochure.pdf\">Get Brochure<\/a><\/b><\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-table is-style-stripes\"><table><thead><tr><th><\/th><th class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"><strong>CORE COURSES<\/strong><\/th><th><\/th><\/tr><\/thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>CODE<\/strong><\/td><td class=\"has-text-align-left\" data-align=\"left\"><strong>DESCRIPTIVE TITLE<\/strong><\/td><td><strong>UNITS<\/strong><